] <tab:targets>

The parser labels are not perfect proxies for linguistic categories. For this reason, each
construction family is treated as a measurable approximation. The interpretation of results is
therefore conservative: a significant effect indicates a change in parser-detected structure, not
necessarily a complete linguistic theory of the model's syntax.

== Generation Protocol

Each prompt was sent to the model with temperature set to a moderate value. Very low
temperature makes outputs too deterministic and can hide distributional effects. Very high
temperature adds noise and makes parsing less reliable. The chosen setting balances variation
with coherence.

For each prompt pair, multiple responses were generated. Responses were discarded if they
failed to answer the probe, contained fewer than a minimum number of tokens, or copied a
large fragment of the context. The remaining responses were parsed and converted into
construction counts.

The primary outcome is the difference in normalized construction rate between the aligned and
control conditions. Secondary outcomes include response length, parse failure rate, and
qualitative error categories. As in many model-evaluation settings, the analysis treats
performance estimates as noisy signals rather than final judgments #cite("yao2023predictinggeneralizationperformancecorrectness").

