=== Reliability Checks

The annotation pipeline includes several reliability checks. A random sample of responses is
inspected manually, and the manual notes are compared with detector outputs. The goal is not
to produce a full gold standard, but to identify systematic detector failures before interpreting
the aggregate results.

The most common errors involve sentence boundaries and reduced clauses. Sentence-boundary
errors can make a construction appear to span more material than it actually does. Reduced
clauses can be hard to distinguish from adjectival modifiers. These cases are flagged rather
than silently folded into the main counts.

#figure(caption: [Manual validation workflow for parser-derived counts.])[
  #sample-figure(
    [Sample responses -> manual notes -> detector comparison -> revised filters],
    [The workflow is lightweight, but it catches recurring parser and segmentation errors.]
  )
] <fig:validation>

== Dataset Summary

The final sample contains prompt pairs distributed across four construction families. Each pair
contributes one aligned condition and one control condition. Multiple responses are generated
for each condition, which makes it possible to estimate variation across runs as well as across
prompt items.

The dataset is intentionally small enough to inspect. Large automatically generated datasets
can hide annotation failures, while very small datasets make effect estimates unstable. The
sample size used here is meant to balance those concerns for a thesis-scale experiment.

